      protected void displayUsersGuide()

The path cab be set in the program Preferences dialog.This command is executed in a separate thread since it may take a noticeable amount time to complete, and by using a separate thread the GUI is allowed to continue to update

    • importFileInBackground

      protected void importFileInBackground(CcddClassesComponent.FileEnvVar[] dataFile, boolean importingEntireDatabase, boolean backupFirst, boolean replaceExistingTables, boolean appendExistingFields, boolean useExistingFields, boolean openEditor, boolean ignoreErrors, boolean replaceExistingMacros, boolean replaceExistingGroups, boolean replaceExistingAssociations, boolean deleteNonExistingTables, boolean replaceExistingDataTypes, CcddConstants.FileExtension importFileType, CcddConstants.ManagerDialogType dialogType, List<String[]> usersAndAccessLevel, Component parent)
      Import one or more files, creating new tables and optionally replacing existing ones. The file(s) may contain definitions for more than one table. This method is executed in a separate thread since it can take a noticeable amount time to complete, and by using a separate thread the GUI is allowed to continue to update. The GUI menu commands, however, are disabled until the database method completes execution
      Parameters:
      dataFile - Array of files to import
      importingEntireDatabase - Is an entire database being imported?
      backupFirst - True to create a backup of the database before importing tables
      replaceExistingTables - True to replace a table that already exists in the database
      appendExistingFields - True to append the existing data fields for a table (if any) to the imported ones (if any). Only valid when replaceExisting is true
      useExistingFields - True to use an existing data field in place of the imported ones if the field names match. Only valid when replaceExisting and appendExistingFields are true
      openEditor - True to open a table editor for each imported table
      ignoreErrors - True to ignore all errors in the import file
      replaceExistingMacros - True to replace the values for existing macros
      replaceExistingGroups - True to replace existing group definitions
      replaceExistingAssociations - True to overwrite internal associations with those from the import file
      deleteNonExistingTables - True to delete any tables from the database that were not part of the import
      replaceExistingDataTypes - True to replace existing data types that share a name with an imported data type
      importFileType - The extension for what type of file is being imported
      dialogType - The type of file import being performed
      parent - GUI component over which to center any error dialog
      usersAndAccessLevel - List of users and their access levels

    • importFiles

      protected boolean importFiles(List<CcddClassesComponent.FileEnvVar> dataFiles, boolean backupFirst, boolean importingEntireDatabase, boolean replaceExistingTables, boolean appendExistingFields, boolean useExistingFields, boolean openEditor, boolean ignoreErrors, boolean replaceExistingMacros, boolean replaceExistingAssociations, boolean replaceExistingGroups, boolean replaceExistingDataTypes, CcddConstants.ManagerDialogType fileType, Component parent)
      Import one or more files, creating new tables and optionally replacing existing ones. The file(s) may contain definitions for more than one table. This method is executed in a separate thread since it can take a noticeable amount time to complete, and by using a separate thread the GUI is allowed to continue to update. The GUI menu commands, however, are disabled until the database method completes execution
      Parameters:
      dataFiles - Array of files to import
      backupFirst - True to create a backup of the database before importing tables
      importingEntireDatabase - True if the entire database is being imported
      replaceExistingTables - True to replace a table that already exists in the database
      appendExistingFields - True to append the existing data fields for a table (if any) to the imported ones (if any). Only valid when replaceExisting is true
      useExistingFields - True to use an existing data field in place of the imported ones if the field names match. Only valid when replaceExisting and appendExistingFields are true
      openEditor - True to open a table editor for each imported table
      ignoreErrors - True to ignore all errors in the import file
      replaceExistingMacros - True to replace the values for existing macros
      replaceExistingAssociations - True to overwrite internal associations with those from the import file
      replaceExistingGroups - True to replace existing group definitions
      replaceExistingDataTypes - True to replace existing data types that share a name with an imported data type
      fileType - Import file type: IMPORT_CSV, IMPORT_EDS,IMPORT_JSON, or IMPORT_XTCE
      parent - GUI component over which to center any error dialog
      Returns:
      True if the import operation completes successfully

    • createImportedTable

      private boolean createImportedTable(CcddClassesDataTable.TableInfo tableInfo, List<String> cellData, int numColumns, boolean replaceExisting, boolean openEditor, List<String> allTables, boolean lastTableDefn, boolean isRootTable, boolean ignoreErrors, Component parent) throws CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException
      Create a new data table or replace an existing one and paste the supplied cell data into it
      Parameters:
      tableInfo - Table information for the table to create
      cellData - Array containing the cell data
      numColumns - Number of columns in the table
      replaceExisting - True to replace a table that already exists in the database
      openEditor - True to open a table editor for each imported table
      allTables - List containing the paths and names of all tables
      lastTableDefn - Is this the last table definition to be imported?
      isRootTable - Does the tableInfo belong to a root table? If 'lastTableDefn' is true the value of 'isRootTable' does not matter.
      ignoreErrors - Should errors be ignored
      parent - GUI component over which to center any error dialog
      Returns:
      True if the table is successfully imported; false if the table exists and the replaceExisting flag is not true
      Throws:
      CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException - The existing table that the new table replaces cannot be removed, the new table cannot be created, or the data cannot be added to the newly created table

    • exportSelectedTablesInBackground

      protected void exportSelectedTablesInBackground(String filePath, String[] tablePaths, boolean overwriteFile, boolean singleFile, boolean includeBuildInformation, boolean replaceMacros, boolean deleteTargetDirectory, boolean includeAllTableTypes, boolean includeAllDataTypes, boolean includeAllInputTypes, boolean includeAllMacros, boolean includeReservedMsgIDs, boolean includeProjectFields, boolean includeGroups, boolean includeAssociations, boolean includeTlmSched, boolean includeAppSched, boolean includeVariablePaths, CcddVariableHandler variableHandler, String[] separators, CcddConstants.FileExtension fileExtn, CcddConstants.EndianType endianess, boolean isHeaderBigEndian, String version, String validationStatus, String classification, Component parent)
      Export the contents of one or more tables selected by the user to one or more files in the specified format. The export file names are based on the table name if each table is stored in a separate file. The user supplied file name is used if multiple tables are stored in a single file. This method is executed in a separate thread since it can take a noticeable amount time to complete, and by using a separate thread the GUI is allowed to continue to update. The GUI menu commands, however, are disabled until the database method completes execution
      Parameters:
      filePath - Path to the folder in which to store the exported tables. Includes the name if storing the tables to a single file
      tablePaths - Table path for each table to load
      overwriteFile - True to store overwrite an existing file; false skip exporting a table to a file that already exists
      singleFile - True to store multiple tables in a single file; false to store each table in a separate file
      includeBuildInformation - True to include the CCDD version, project, host, and user information
      replaceMacros - True to replace macros with their corresponding values; false to leave the macros intact
      deleteTargetDirectory - True to delete the target directory contents
      includeAllTableTypes - True to include the all table type definitions in the export file
      includeAllDataTypes - True to include the all data type definitions in the export file
      includeAllInputTypes - True to include the all user-defined input type definitions in the export file
      includeAllMacros - True to include the all macro definitions in the export file
      includeReservedMsgIDs - True to include the contents of the reserved message ID table in the export file
      includeProjectFields - True to include the project-level data field definitions in the export file
      includeGroups - True to include the groups and group data field definitions in the export file
      includeAssociations - True to include the script associations in the export file
      includeTlmSched - True to include the telemetry scheduler entries in the export file
      includeAppSched - True to include the application scheduler entries in the export file
      includeVariablePaths - True to include the variable path for each variable in a structure table, both in application format and using the user-defined separator characters
      variableHandler - Variable handler class reference; null if includeVariablePaths is false
      separators - String array containing the variable path separator character(s), show/hide data types flag ('true' or 'false'), and data type/variable name separator character(s); null if includeVariablePaths is false
      fileExtn - File extension type
      endianess - EndianType.BIG_ENDIAN for big endian, EndianType.LITTLE_ENDIAN for little endian
      isHeaderBigEndian - True if the telemetry and command headers are always big endian (e.g., as with CCSDS)
      version - Version attribute (XTCE only)
      validationStatus - Validation status attribute (XTCE only)
      classification - Classification attribute (XTCE only)
      parent - GUI component over which to center any error dialog

      includeVariablePaths - True to include the variable path for each variable in a structure table, both in application format and using the user-defined separator characters
      variableHandler - Variable handler class reference; null if includeVariablePaths is false
      separators - String array containing the variable path separator character(s), show/hide data types flag ('true' or 'false'), and data type/variable name separator character(s); null if includeVariablePaths is false
      fileExtn - File extension type
      endianess - EndianType.BIG_ENDIAN for big endian, EndianType.LITTLE_ENDIAN for little endian
      isHeaderBigEndian - True if the telemetry and command headers are always big endian (e.g., as with CCSDS)
      version - Version attribute (XTCE only)
      validationStatus - Validation status attribute (XTCE only)
      classification - Classification attribute (XTCE only)
      parent - GUI component over which to center any error dialog
      Returns:
      True if the export completes successfully

    • prepareJsonOrCsvImport

      protected boolean prepareJsonOrCsvImport(CcddClassesComponent.FileEnvVar[] dataFiles, boolean importingEntireDatabase, boolean backupFirst, boolean replaceExistingTables, boolean appendExistingFields, boolean useExistingFields, boolean openEditor, boolean ignoreErrors, boolean replaceExistingMacros, boolean replaceExistingAssociations, boolean replaceExistingGroups, boolean replaceExistingDataTypes, boolean deleteNonExistingTables, CcddConstants.FileExtension importFileType, CcddConstants.ManagerDialogType dialogType, Component parent)
      This function will accept a file or files with JSON/CSV format. It will look thorough the files and determine if they contain data that is not currently in the database. If so it will call an import function on this data. If the files to be imported are in agreement with the current state of the database this will be reported and nothing will be imported
      Parameters:
      dataFiles - The files being imported
      importingEntireDatabase - Is an entire database being imported?
      backupFirst - True to create a backup of the database before importing tables
      replaceExistingTables - True to replace a table that already exists in the database
      appendExistingFields - True to append the existing data fields for a table (if any) to the imported ones (if any). Only valid when replaceExisting is true
      useExistingFields - True to use an existing data field in place of the imported ones if the field names match. Only valid when replaceExisting and appendExistingFields are true
      openEditor - True to open a table editor for each imported table
      ignoreErrors - True to ignore all errors in the import file
      replaceExistingMacros - True to replace the values for existing macros
      replaceExistingAssociations - True to overwrite internal associations with those from the import file
      replaceExistingGroups - True to replace the values for existing groups
      replaceExistingDataTypes - True to replace existing data types that share a name with an imported data type
      deleteNonExistingTables - True to delete any tables from the database that were not part of the import
      importFileType - The extension for the file type being imported
      dialogType - What type of file is being imported
      parent - GUI component over which to center any error dialog
      Returns:
      True if an error occurred importing
